To study the reaction mechanism of NIR-SO2-TP to NaHSO3, the addition of NaHSO3 to NIR-SO2-TP was conducted by 1H NMR titration experiment. Once NIR-SO2-TP exposed to NaHSO3 (Fig. 2
                        ), a new resonance signal loaded at around 4.1 ppm (Ha´) along with the signal of CC double band (Ha, about 8.2 ppm) fading away, which testified the formation of the new compound of NIR-SO2-TP-HSO3
                        − adduct. To further verify the sensing mechanism, the ESI-MS analysis (Fig. S4) of NIR-SO2-TP treated with NaHSO3 was characterized as well, where a new peak appeared at m/z 623.1988 of [M−H]– (calca. = 623.1988) was clearly obtained. The above statistics are accordant with the sensing mechanism in Scheme 1.
